beer.beer_description:
While lazing about remembering the good ol’ days of the great south west… we’ve brewed a big Hazy IPA packed full of Citra, El Dorado and Mosaic hops
– it’s hazy IPA at its best.

Mild bitterness followed by good fruity esters boosted from a low flocculating English yeast. A cloudy and light malt base helps juice up this sessionable 5.8% Hazy IPA that has been hopped multiple times through the process.
